Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve, attracting more than 500 kinds of wildlife cities to "settle"
2020-07-26 05:03:17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sisuo Responsibility Editor: Wang Sisuo
The natural ecology of the capital continues to improve, attracting wildlife cities to "settle"
There are more than 500 species of wild animals in Beijing.
Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Bureau of Landscaping that in recent years, with the continuous improvement of the natural ecological environment of the capital, the types and number of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wildlife living in Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including national-level protected animals such as brown horse chickens and black storks, as well as secondary protected animals such as antelopes, large swans, gray cranes, and ducks.
Whether it is a city forest planted in the second ring, or a small micro-wetland embedded in the building, it not only brings the wild interest of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wild animals to "settle" in the city.
In the middle of summer, it is located in the Songshan National Nature Reserve in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District.
One of the squirrels played leisurely beside the mountains, and two dogs and thugs fought each other.
Looking back, a wild boar can't help but "sting" on his body, and is rubbing the bark. Hu Qiaoli, director of the Matsuyama National Nature Reserve Management Department, introduced that by the end of 2019, in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, there were 178 species of wild animals, including the national protection of animal gold carvings and national secondary protection of spoon chickens and lantels, and nearly one-third of the city's wildlife species can be found here.
"In Songshan, wild animals are the real 'masters', and our staff can only be regarded as people's 'guards' at best."
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the situation of wild animals and plants in the protected area on the ground, more than 30 professional patrol members are patrolling along 16 carefully formulated protection routes every day, and there will be a "turning circle" every month, and almost walking through the entire protected area in a whole day.
“At the time of inspection, it is not only necessary to check the recording of biodiversity, but also to check the installation of artificial bird nests, rescue injured wild animals, install infrared cameras in the wild, and so on.”
Songshan National Nature Reserve has installed more than 200 infrared cameras to record the living status of wild animals in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli introduced that with the continuous enrichment of biodiversity in the protected areas in recent years, more and more wild animals have appeared in the lens, leopard cats, squatters and pigsters have become "resident guests", and the "out-of-the-box rate" of national secondary protection animals is getting higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, director of the wildlife and wetland protection department of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Landscaping and Landscaping, said that Beijing's terrestrial vertebrae wildlife has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 species, and the species and number of wild animals in Beijing have continued to increase in recent years.
The presence of wild animals in cities is becoming more common, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of the capital city in recent years.
In particular, a new round of afforestation and greening construction of one million mu began in 2018, proposing to reshape the urban ecological environment, improve the ecological function of forest green space, and highlight the concept of "near nature".
The plan strives to interact with the surrounding green space to facilitate the "visiting relatives and friends" of wild animals, and the trees are also the favorite honey and food plants of animals.
Black land "sow" out of agricultural modernization - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26th: Black land "sows" agricultural modernization
In the summer, two spraying pharmaceutical aircraft swept over the 10,000-acre high-yield demonstration field of the second operation station of the Fifth Management Zone of the Friendship Farm, forming two white lines, and the "first match in the world" with black rice seedlings in the green field was particularly eye-catching.
The station manager of this operating station, Kong Lingqiang, said that this aircraft can spray more than 6,000 acres of arable land a day, which is about 8 times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times that of artificial labor.
This farm is located in the territory of Heilongjiang Province, China's first grain-producing province, and from the past "sun" rice cutting sound through to the current "rumbling" motor sound, Chinese traditional farming and farms in this black soil belt to achieve transformation.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in modern agricultural production on Friendship Farms.
On the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural inputs, and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standardized operation level of agricultural machinery in the field.
In this year's rice production process, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned cutting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes the seedlings plant more even, which can maximize the utilization of sunlight and arable land resources, and save 16 yuan per acre of labor costs.
Farms have tried new technologies such as informationization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total number of farm agricultural machinery is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the field is 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operations to achieve GPS satellite navigation 100%, dry field precision sowing 100%, dry field high-horsepower locomotive operation 100%.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture, digital agriculture is the direction of agricultural modernization."
The president of the Friendship Farm, Liu Hualian, said.
The key to agricultural modernization is scientific and technological progress.
Heilongjiang agricultural reclamation, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large-scale agricultural "carriers" in recent years, and initially established a modern agricultural industry system led by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery exhibition park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
Here, more than 140 (pieces) of agricultural machinery have been introduced and used by Heilongjiang agricultural reclamation over the years.
These agricultural machinery and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
