International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious trouble to China-US relations, and China has responded to the unreasonable provocations taken by the United States, and it is legitimate and necessary to take countermeasures.
Andrés Borks, director of the China Studies Center at the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateralist measures of the United States have damaged the bridge of understanding between the two peoples and caused a crisis in the relations between the two major countries.
China's notification of the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to unilateral measures by the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the University of Argentina and director of the Center for Argentine-Chinese Studies, said that China's decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocation of the United States, and is not aimed at ordinary American people.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American people by putting pressure on China to cover up its weak response to the new crown epidemic.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the United States has taken a provocative diplomatic stance, causing serious problems in bilateral relations between China and the United States, and facing serious challenges in bilateral relations.
China's notification to the United States that the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal counter-measure, in line with diplomatic practice, which reflects both China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests and the reasonable and favorable interests of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian commentator Francis Semwenza said China's decision was a legitimate and necessary response to the provocations made by the United States.
China-US relations should return to normal, and the US should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how it can win economic and political win-win results with China and how it can benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Yusuf, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures that China has been forced to take are a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable behavior of the United States, in line with international law and basic norms of international relations, and in line with diplomatic practice.
Earlier, the US called for the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston to seriously violate international law and basic norms governing international relations.
It is hoped that the US side will rescind the previous relevant decision and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's "Lianhe Zaobao" published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the US's step-by-step efforts, although China is very reluctant to see Sino-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
