In response to the US Department of Commerce recently announced that it decided to launch an anti-dumping and anti-subsidy investigation on products originating in China, and launched an investigation on the "RMB exchange rate undervaluation" project.
China's Ministry of Commerce pointed out that this is the first time that the United States has investigated the so-called "yuan exchange rate undervaluation" project in the neutral case of the countervailing case, and China firmly opposes it.
China's Ministry of Commerce issued a special press release on the evening of the 23rd, saying that China's implementation of a market-based supply and demand, reference to a basket of currencies for adjustment, managed floating exchange rate system, the market in the formation of the exchange rate plays a decisive role.
The press release stressed that, in general, the RMB exchange rate is at a reasonable equilibrium level and is not undervalued.
Since 2005, the RMB has appreciated by more than 17% against the US dollar.
According to data released by the Bank for International Settlements, from the beginning of 2005 to May 2020, the effective exchange rate of the renminbi will appreciate by 38%, and the real effective exchange rate will appreciate by 49%, which is the strongest currency in the G20 economy and one of the most appreciated currencies in the world.
The Ministry of Commerce pointed out that the exchange rate issue exceeded the authority of members to conduct countervailing investigations in accordance with the rules of the World Trade Organization.
The United States amended its regulations in February this year to conduct a countervailing investigation into the exchange rates of other countries, which has been suspected of violating WTO rules and has been opposed by many parties.
The press release said that even according to U.S. regulations, there are a large number of errors in the content of the applicant's complaint, and there are no necessary elements for countervailing subsidies such as financial support, profit awarding and specificity.
China urges the US to abide by existing international rules and stop countervailing investigations into the so-called “undervaluation of the RMB exchange rate.”
