Shenzhen to publicly solicit opinions on the introduction of health regulations - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporter Mao Siqian, Bai Yu) encourage residents to do physical examinations and detect problems early; prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish an online game health review system; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel... Recently, the "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft for Comment)" was officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to do physical examinations and detect problems at an early stage, the above-mentioned draft for comment proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination projects according to different ages, occupations and other factors.
The cost of a health examination within the scope of the basic catalogue of the health examination project shall be paid by the Social Medical Insurance Co-ordinator Fund in accordance with the standard of one per person per year.
The draft for comment clearly states that the employer should rationally allocate human resources, arrange staff working time, and implement a rest system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor load, so as to avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health injuries to the health of employees, and strictly implement the employee paid leave system.
In addition, the employer should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize the implementation of employee health examination.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for comment proposes to prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors, while restricting the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages, and for violating the regulations, the market supervision and management department will order the correction and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "banning alcohol", minors should also "multiple sports".
According to the requirements of the draft for comment, the school should arrange student sports activities for more than one hour per day.
For online games, public security, cultural radio and television tourism, sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet Internet service places, establish an online game health review system, and create a good communication space and communication culture for the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks in public places, and medical and health institutions will be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft for comment also requires that before formulating plans and normative documents such as urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization and ecological environment protection, biomedical industry development, and approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects, the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population should be assessed.
If it is not evaluated or evaluated, it will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents, it shall not be formulated or approved for implementation.
