Cocosiri Tibetan antelope enters the return season - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, July 25 (Reporter Wang Jinjin) The reporter learned from the five-way beam protection station of the Cocosiri Management Department of the Yangtze River Source Park of Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration that the monitoring showed that the Tibetan antelope that had previously gone to the neighboring chips in the Lake Zhuo Nai area of Cocosiri was ending the birth of litters and began to return to their original habitat with their cubs.
Surveillance screen near the five beam protection station shows that on July 25, about 40 female Tibetan antelopes led three Tibetan antelope cubs through the Qinghai-Tibet Highway 3002 kilometers, the Qinghai-Tibet Railway Wulong North Bridge, and the Tibetan antelope has begun to move back.
According to expert analysis, in recent years, the number of Tibetan antelope cubs in the returning flock accounted for one-fourth to one-fifth of the total number of Tibetan antelope sheep.
Lian Xinming, an associate researcher at the Northwest Plateau Biology Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said: “In the early days of the relocation, Tibetan antelopes are at higher risk of being arrested and eaten, so the number of cubs in the flock will be less, and there may even be no cubs.”
According to the statistics of the Cocosiri Management Department of the Yangtze River Source Park of the Sanjiangyuan National Park Administration, the overall number of Tibetan antelope relocations has increased year by year, and the number of Tibetan antelope relocations in 2019 was 4,860, an increase of 338 over 2018.
Lian Xinming said: "It is expected that the return of Tibetan antelope this year will end in early September, and the number of returning Tibetan antelope is still expected to continue to increase."
Tibetan antelope is a protected animal at the national level.
Every year at the end of May, Tibetan antelopes from Qinghai Sanjiangyuan, Qiangtang, Tibet, Xinjiang Aljin Mountain and other places are required to go to the Law of Zhuo Nai, located in the hinterland of Cocosiri.
Wu Xiaomin, an expert on the protection of Tibetan antelopes in China and a researcher at the Shaanxi Provincial Animal Research Institute (Northwest Institute of Endangered Animals), said: "The return of the Tibetan antelope is the process of returning to the habitat with the cubs after the female Tibetan antelope is returned to their habitat after the return of the female Tibetan antelope.
In order to ensure the safe relocation of Tibetan antelope flocks, the reporter learned that the Cocosiri Management Office of the Yangtze River Source Park of Sanjiangyuan National Park has arranged for staff to continue to carry out video monitoring and patrol in the main relocation area.
If it is found that there are Tibetan antelope flocks trying to cross the road, the mountain rangers will carry out temporary traffic control in the first time, so that the flock can safely pass through the wildlife passageway and ensure that they are as little human interference as possible during the relocation.
So, how to relieve the heat in daily life?
Experts suggest that summer out to avoid the high temperature period, it is best not to walk or work in the hot sun around noon, because the sunshine of this time period is the strongest, the possibility of heat stroke is higher.
If you must go out at this time, you must do a good job of protection, such as wearing a parasol, wearing a sun hat, wearing sunglasses, and applying sunscreen to prevent sunburn.
Clothing as far as possible to choose light, good breathable cotton, hemp, silk texture, less wearing chemical fiber clothing, so as not to sweat a lot of time when not timely heat dissipation, causing heat stroke.
When hot and hot weather, be prepared to drink enough water, drink it in time, do not wait for thirst to drink water, because once you feel thirsty, it means that the body is already short of water, each time the water is controlled at 150 ml to 200 ml, drink warm water, do not drink ice water.
According to the temperature, the general personnel drink 1.5 to 2 liters of water every day, and the high-temperature workers drink 3 to 5 liters of water every day.
When sweating more, you can properly supplement some salt water to make up for the salt lost by the human body due to sweating.
In addition, the human body is prone to lack of potassium in the summer, making people feel tired and tired, and containing potassium tea is an excellent summer drink.
In the summer, eat more fruits and vegetables with high water content, such as lettuce, cucumbers, tomatoes, etc.; fresh fruits, such as peaches, apricots, watermelons, melons, etc., can be used to supplement water; dairy products can not only replenish water, but also to meet the nutritional needs of the body.
In addition, people who work in high-temperature environments should be supplemented with drinks containing potassium, magnesium and other elements.
In summer, the day and night are short, the temperature is high, the human body's metabolism is strong, the consumption is also large, and it is easy to feel fatigue.
Adequate sleep can relax the brain and body systems, which is conducive to work and study, and is also a measure to prevent heat stroke.
Experts say the best time to go to bed is from 22:00 to 23:00, and the best time to get up is from 5:30 to 6:30.
When sleeping, be careful not to lie under the air conditioning outlet and electric fan, so as not to suffer from air conditioning disease and heat injury.
