France to increase military investment in space - Xinhua
French Defense Minister Florence Parly said on the 24th that France will add hundreds of millions of euros to the space defense budget and develop space military forces to prevent other countries from making "unfriendly actions" in outer space.
Parly told Provence that between 2019 and 2025, the budget for French space military projects will increase from the previously proposed 3.6 billion euros ($4.2 billion) to 4.3 billion euros ($5 billion).
According to the French Military Planning Act 2019-2025 approved by the French Parliament in 2018, France is expected to update the existing observation satellites and communication satellites in the future, launch three electromagnetic listening satellites, and improve the modernization of space surveillance radar.
French President Emmanuel Macron announced in July last year that a military command and an “aviation and space force” would be established within the French Air Force.
Parly said she would officially announce the creation of the Space Force when she visits a military academy in Salon, Provence, later.
Parley said the Space Force is part of the Air Force and will have 500 personnel by 2025.
“The idea that space used to serve the common good of science is gone,” she said. “Space is now the place where nations compete for global hegemony.”
Parly reiterated Macron's previous statement, saying that the French side has no intention of provoking an arms race.
“We are not engaged in an arms race. But I have a responsibility to fully recognize the threat we may face.”
Parly reintroduces the surveillance of a military satellite shared by France and Italy in 2017.
She said the “peeping” was a Russian satellite.
The Russian side denied this claim.
Parley said France would soon have small patrol satellites capable of detecting and locking in "the black hands behind those unfriendly moves."
French media believe that the reason why France is seeking to set up a space force is because US President Donald Trump asked the US Department of Defense in February last year to draft a bill to establish a space force.
Trump signed a defense authorization bill in December that approved the creation of the sixth largest service in the United States, the Space Force.
Some experts worry that these measures by the United States have accelerated the pace of US space militarization and may trigger a new space arms race.
