Report says shared accommodation market has picked up since March
The "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, in the first five months of 2020, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market fell by 72.1% year-on-year.
However, the shared accommodation market has been warming up since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception have gradually recovered.
The "Report" shows that the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market has dropped significantly, on the one hand, due to the sharp decline in the demand for travel accommodation under the prevention and control of the epidemic, the sharp decline in orders, the total number of orders in the first five months fell by 65% year-on-year, and the number of receptions fell by 63% year-on-year; on the other hand, the weak demand also led to a relatively significant decline in the price of the night, and the average night price in the first five months fell by 16% year-on.
However, in March, April and May, the market turnover increased by 78%, 199% and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50% respectively; the number of receptions increased by 81%, 112% and 28% respectively.
The report pointed out that the development of the shared accommodation industry has been promising for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, told the "Workers Daily" reporter that the development of shared accommodation needs more powerful policies to support, on the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job in the implementation of the policies that have been issued in the early stage, further strengthen policy promotion, and focus on creating a better business environment; on the other hand, it is necessary to further strengthen policy guidance and support from various aspects such as stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovating services, and strengthening cooperation with government and platform enterprises.
