"In the process of project construction, we have advanced geological forecasting in the use of geological survey methods, object detection methods and advanced drilling methods, and have adopted special design solutions for more than 30 types of caves. For example, a 24-meter-long bridge has been designed and built, and large caves with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel have been designed to avoid tunnel subsidence," the Royal Army said.
