Economic Daily · China Economic Net reporter Lin Fire Can
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China's overall promotion of epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development, the epidemic prevention and control situation is constantly improving, the steady recovery of the economy is obvious, the employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood are generally stable, and China's economy has handed over a temperature economic operation report card.
In the first two months of this year, the survey unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, many enterprises' production and business activities were basically in a state of shutdown, the demand for enterprise employment was reduced, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the unemployment rate of urban surveys increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the order of production and life in the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of steady progress, further increases the hedging of macro policies, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting and stabilizing jobs and expanding employment.
China has increased its policy of hedging and stabilizing positions, playing a combination of "relief and rebate" policies, phased in the reduction of the payment part of 3 social insurance units, allowing the deferred payment of social insurance premiums, expanding the steady return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises, benefiting from the work-based training policy, and giving absorption subsidies and apprenticeship subsidies to enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various stable employment policies, the demand for employment of enterprises has steadily rebounded, the employment situation has gradually improved, the urban survey unemployment rate has gradually declined, and in June, the survey unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Population and Employment Statistics Department of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to be effective, and the labor force that withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic returned in the early period, and the labor force participation rate in urban areas in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which was close to the level of the same period last year.
Data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average working week of enterprise employees reached 46.8 hours, an increase of 6.6 hours from February and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, a new high in many years.
Entering February, although the CPI year-on-year growth rate fell slightly, but it is still in the "5 range".
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, both the factors driving consumer demand before the Spring Festival, and the factors of the wrong month of the Spring Festival and the low base of the year-on-year.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the epidemic prevention and control, in January and February, there were logistics delays, illuctimate supply of materials, and increased material transportation costs, and some citizens hoarded and sold, and the price of some necessities rose significantly.
In order to cope with the disturbances caused by the epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the influence of a series of policy measures, the supply of vegetable melon and fruit market is strongly guaranteed.
In order to cope with the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government introduced a policy of ensuring stable prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, the supply of pork reserves improved significantly, the production capacity of pigs was restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and sales was gradually normal.
Since March, pork prices have fallen continuously, and in May, the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6%; in June, pork prices rose slightly month-on-month due to factors such as the slowdown in pig exports, the reduction of imports and the rebound in group consumption demand.
The seasonal change in fresh vegetable prices is obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the higher base of comparison in the same period last year, fresh fruit prices continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic life of the masses is effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation is stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation logistics, the supply and demand of the market have improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level has returned to stable.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, and the overall inflation pressure is not large, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and life order under the premise of doing a good job in the normalization of epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main producing areas of agricultural products such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on acts that disturb market order such as hoarding and raising prices.
