Before volunteering to fill in the report, first understand what is the professional level difference - Zhongxin
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yuxiao Responsibility Editor: Yuxiao
Before volunteering, understand what is a professional level difference.
Every year, students or parents do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary report, and then affect the voluntary filling.
This year, five universities, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued a 2020 enrollment policy to cancel the professional grade difference.
What does professional difference mean and what is the significance of volunteering?
There are three types of professional allocation rules.
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteer, we must read the enrollment charter of the school of our choice in detail, and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of tranches, professional allocation rules, etc.
Professional allocation rules refer to the three ways after the transfer of colleges and universities, there are three main ways of professional priority, score priority, and professional grade difference for professional admission.
The specific way of use of colleges and universities will be clear in the Admissions Charter.
However, there are also some colleges and universities that have the principle of admission that are given overall priority, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates will queue according to the total score within the admission range, when the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score line, it will see whether the second professional volunteer admission score line is reached, and so on until the admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" is that when the college arranges the candidate's professional, according to the one or several points published in the enrollment charter, it is determined to select the admission profession of different professional volunteer candidates, which is "professional grade difference".
That is to say, the difference in the score of the college in the admission of candidates for the first professional volunteer and non-first professional volunteer, the difference between the students, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 points, etc.
For example.
Assuming that the students Xiaoming applied to A colleges and universities and took 560 points, their professional volunteers were: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, and the professional admission of A university implemented the professional level difference, and the grade difference was divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, 0 points.
In the professional allocation, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and has a planned balance of the professional, then Xiaoming is admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, according to the score of 558 points and the first professional volunteer to apply for "international trade" ranking, to determine whether it meets the professional admission conditions; if it is still not satisfied, the score is subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for the third professional volunteer "automation" admission; if it is still not satisfied with the third professional volunteer "automation"; if it is still not satisfied with the third professional volunteer "automation"; if it is still not satisfied with the third professional volunteer "automation"; if it is still not satisfied with the third professional volunteer "automation"; if it is still not satisfied with the third professional volunteer "compulsion"; if it is still not enough to meet the third professional volunteer "automation"; if it is still not satisfied.By way, and so on.
Different University Professional Level Differential Settings
With the popularity of parallel volunteerism, many colleges and universities have now cancelled the professional grade difference, but this year there are still some colleges and universities have retained this method, from the school's announcement of the "enrollment charter" point of view, this year, there are mainly more than 20 universities set up professional grade difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight College and so on.
In these colleges and universities, the professional grade difference set by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University, the file has been cast to the school candidates, according to the order of candidates to fill in the professional volunteer order after the reduction of 1 points by the ranking of admission.
And some universities have different professional levels between different majors.
For example, the total score of the professional volunteer level is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteer level is 3 points, the difference between other professional volunteers is not set, as parallel volunteer, and the professional level difference between other professional volunteers and adjustment professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in the volunteer, candidates and parents must carefully read the school's admission policy, to see if there is no professional grade difference, the form of poor grade is what, in full consideration of the score at the same time, but also a reasonable analysis of the proposed school and professional, if the college in the admissions charter clearly adopt the score level difference method for admission, candidates in the selection of professional, pay attention to the gradient between the majors, improve the admission rate.
